g Member</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:16:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Complete Heal</span><hr size=1> OK, question here.  I see people all over posting that they think complete heal was a mistake, a design flaw, or should for some reason be removed from the game.<br>
<br>
Why?!?<br>
<br>
I don't understand why people dislike the spell, in my opinion, it's one of the greatest things that could have happened to everquest.  It means that to keep a main tank up it requires skill and timing not just random spamming of heals.  It makes encounters more skill dependent and less zerg dependent.  It makes gear upgrades (most notably on tanks) actually matter.<br>
<br>
The primary reason that it matters how many hp a tank has is that the heal output produced by complete heal is directly tied to it.  Before I had complete heal with my cleric, I never bothered to buff tank hp.  It didn't matter, because without complete heal, there is no real advantage.<br>
<br>
Anyways, maybe I'm missing something, but I have no clue why people bitch about this spell, so please enlighten me.<br>
<br>
Ammelen, 60 Sorceror<br>
Ezelar, 60 Phantasmist<br>
Boradek, 56 Templar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saalron>Saalron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 595<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:57:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> Cheal is simply the most effective healing spell. By a lot. Every late game encounter is run with a chain of cheals.<br>
<br>
Take a look at wizard nukes. There is no percentage based nuke. That would become overpowered for it's mana cost when used as time goes on as mudflation will cause mobs to have more hp as time goes on. The same holds true for dots, buffs, and every other spell. There is no damage shield that hits for 0.1% of a mob's life each time. It would be too overpowered, you would have to completely tune every encounter around the fact that the players would design their strategy around it.<br>
<br>
Much like we do with cheal.<br>
<br>
Once you are in the end game, who gives a fuck what the mana ratio on Chloroblast, Nature's Heal, Superior Heal, Divine Light, Elixir, etc. is? They all aren't cheal. So fuck them for late game encounters unless they are part of a 'rotation chain'. Like /elixirtorpor on a mage who makes rods.<br>
<br>
You might say.. but we could never survive some of these encounters in Velious/Luclin without a cheal chain! Guess why that is? It's because cheal was there first and the developers made those encounters demand a cheal chain.<br>
<br>
So now, instead of having a mix of adventurers come along to have a fun encounter, you have to have a warrior with defensive (another percentage modifier which was a design error) and you have to have 3+ clerics. Some content is 'off limits' without at least that; some classes are unvalued in comparison because of that.<br>
<br>
No single ability or spell should be that game defining without serious drawbacks. Much in the same way that mana burn is defined. No longer can they make a mob who has hit points that 4-6 mana burns can destroy it with anything decent lootwise without nagafen/vox code, it wouldn't be content used by the players of the appropriate level, it would just be farm material. Another ability that will impact all the future design for mobs in eq.<br>
<br>
Feign death is another example. Encounters must have 'feignproof' scenarios to not be trivial because of feign.<br>
<br>
Look around, there's a couple more of these poor-design abilities in the game. EQ is not a percentage based game. It's an integer game. Anything that is percentage oriented in EQ will, in time, become either unbalanced or something that you have to design content around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uanikacrystalwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anika Crystalwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Admin Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 1149<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 4:19:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> CHeal is many things.<br>
<br>
It is the most powerful heal in the game.<br>
It is the most efficent heal in the game.<br>
It is the spell that makes 90% of the high end game 'doable'.<br>
<br>
Pretend for a moment that CHeal was replaced with a 2500 point heal.  Think about how that would change encounters.  Verant obviously has (i.e. the Creator and his quite clever 'Balence' curse), and I'd be willing to bet we see a good bit more of other tactics in PoP where CHeal is devalued in some way shape or form.<br>
<br>
Point is, Verant put a spell into the game that is the basis for all encounters.  Everything is balanced against a MT and a CHeal chain save for those Luclin encounters that are designed specifically to make that strategy impractical or troublesome.  There's a reason that focus items don't have any effect on CHeals - even the smallest mana conservation or faster cast time would have massive effects toward reducing the difficulty of Everquest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utotteswede.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotteSwede</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 4:46:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> Yeah, take out cheal so we don´t need 8 clerics for some encounters. We could just bring 50 druids and 40 shammies instead, sounds like a great tradeoff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
