<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Cheal is simply the most effective healing spell. By a lot. Every late game encounter is run with a chain of cheals.<br>
<br>
--Saalron<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It basically boils down to this:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You might say.. but we could never survive some of these encounters in Velious/Luclin without a cheal chain! Guess why that is? It's because cheal was there first and the developers made those encounters demand a cheal chain.<br>
<br>
--Saalron<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Complete Heal, as it is, is the most completely unbalancing spell in the game. It is THE spell that defines the design of all high-end encounters. No other spell has such a far reaching effect on the game. Feign Death (spell and skill) is close. When the level cap for EQ was 50, and the biggest thing you could do was a Naggy/Vox raid, CH was ok. The problem is, as the level cap rose to 60, and HP caps rose as well, CH became WAY too efficient. 400 mana for a spell that can heal &gt;8000 HPs every 12 seconds or so is crazy. Manaburn isn't anywhere near as efficient. In fact, as you get higher in levels, and your tank gets more HPs, CH just gets more and more efficient. Plus, this is a freaking level 39 spell!<br>
<br>
Look at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/data/item.asp?Id=1772">Donal's Chestplate of Mourning</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. The CH cast was nerfed on that item because it was unbelievably unbalancing. (BTW, I love how Casters Realm's description says, Dropped by: Trakanon, and Zone: Coming Soon!)<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> CHeal is many things.<br>
<br>
It is the most powerful heal in the game.<br>
It is the most efficent heal in the game.<br>
It is the spell that makes 90% of the high end game 'doable'.<br>
<br>
--Anika<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Complete Heal is the most powerful heal in the game BECAUSE it is the most efficient heal. It is not only &quot;the spell that makes 90% of the high end game 'doable'&quot;, it is the spell that made 90% of the high-end game the way it is.<br>
<br>
IMO, Complete Heal cannot be taken out of the game. Not anymore. If it were, the whole high-end game would be undoable. Unless every single encounter was re-done to adjust mobs HPs and attacks to re-balance the game, EQ would be truly broken. It would change the whole character of the high-end game without CH. I'm sure ALOT of people would walk away from EQ if this were to happen.<br>
<br>
What about changing the spell? Capping the amount that it heals? Then it wouldn't be a COMPLETE Heal. How about changing the spell to cost more mana, like double or triple the cost, or maybe make it heal as a ratio of mana to HPs healed, like 5 HPs for 1 mana? Then you need to change the HPs and attacks of mobs to reflect the reduced efficiency of the spell, which is alot of mobs and encounters.<br>
<br>
Complete Heal, and it's effect on EQ has defined every encounter since the release of Kunark, maybe even before.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Point is, Verant put a spell into the game that is the basis for all encounters.<br>
<br>
--Anika<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'd say, Verant put a spell into the game that BECAME the basis for all encounters. It didn't start out that way. <p><br>
